item.title: Former Sequoia partner’s new startup uses AI to negotiate your calendar for you
item.dc:creator: Marina Temkin
item.description: Blockit, an AI agent that communicates directly with other calendars, has raised $5 million in seed funding led by Sequoia.

item.title: Palmer Luckey says the coolest thing about Anduril expanding to Long Beach is the fighter jets
item.dc:creator: Julie Bort
item.description: Anduril on Thursday announced its plans to expand its Southern California presence with a major campus in Long Beach, the town where founder Palmer Luckey grew up.

item.title: OpenAI is coming for those sweet enterprise dollars in 2026
item.dc:creator: Rebecca Szkutak
item.description: OpenAI has reportedly appointed Barret Zoph to lead its push into enterprise just a week after Zoph rejoined the company.

item.title: Vimeo starts layoffs after acquisition by Bending Spoons
item.dc:creator: Lucas Ropek
item.description: Vimeo is in the process of laying off some of its global staff after being acquired last year by Bending Spoons for $1.38B.

item.title: GM to end Chevy Bolt EV production next year, move China-made Buick to US factory
item.dc:creator: Kirsten Korosec
item.description: The factory musical chairs reflect an economic and political environment, shaped by the Trump administration's tariff policy and its decision to end the federal EV tax credit.

item.title: Capital One acquires Brex for steep discount to its peak valuation, but early believers are laughing all the way to the bank
item.dc:creator: Connie Loizos
item.description: Before everyone sharpens their knives, consider that for the VCs who backed Brex at its outset, the sale is a triumph.

item.title: Voice AI engine and OpenAI partner LiveKit hits $1B valuation
item.dc:creator: Marina Temkin
item.description: The five-year-old-startup powers OpenAI’s ChatGPT voice mode and raised a $100 million round led by Index Ventures.

item.title: Inference startup Inferact lands $150M to commercialize vLLM
item.dc:creator: Marina Temkin
item.description: The seed round values the newly formed startup at $800 million.

item.title: Are AI agents ready for the workplace? A new benchmark raises doubts
item.dc:creator: Russell Brandom
item.description: New research looks at how leading AI models hold up doing actual white-collar work tasks, drawn from consulting, investment banking, and law. Most models failed.

item.title: Microsoft 365 hit by outage, preventing access to emails and files
item.dc:creator: Zack Whittaker
item.description: An hours-long outage is preventing Microsoft's enterprise customers from accessing their inboxes, files, and video meetings.

item.title: Ring is adding a new content verification feature to videos
item.dc:creator: Sarah Perez
item.description: Ring says the new feature will identify if video edits have been made, even if they're minor.

item.title: Google DeepMind CEO is ‘surprised’ OpenAI is rushing forward with ads in ChatGPT
item.dc:creator: Sarah Perez
item.description: Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis says the tech giant isn't pressuring him to insert ads into the AI chatbot experience.

item.title: Humans& thinks coordination is the next frontier for AI, and they’re building a model to prove it
item.dc:creator: Rebecca Bellan
item.description: Humans&, a new startup founded by alumni of Anthropic, Meta, OpenAI, xAI, and Google DeepMind, is building the next generation of foundation models for collaboration, not chat.

item.title: Substack launches a TV app
item.dc:creator: Aisha Malik
item.description: The move comes as Substack has been investing more heavily in video and livestreaming, as it looks to compete with platforms like YouTube and Patreon for both creators and viewers.

item.title: Tesla launches robotaxi rides in Austin with no human safety driver
item.dc:creator: Rebecca Bellan
item.description: Not all of Tesla's fleet in Austin will be fully driverless. Per Tesla's AI lead Ashok Elluswamy, the company will be "starting with a few unsupervised vehicles mixed in with the broader robotaxi fleet with safety monitors, and the ratio will increase over time."

item.title: Meta seeks to limit evidence in child safety case
item.dc:creator: Lauren Forristal
item.description: Meta is set to go on trial in New Mexico for allegedly failing to protect minors. The company is requesting a broad swath of information not be allowed to be presented in court.

item.title: Google now offers free SAT practice exams, powered by Gemini
item.dc:creator: Lauren Forristal
item.description: Students can prompt Gemini by typing "I want to take a practice SAT test,” and the AI will provide them with a free practice exam. Gemini then analyzes the results, highlighting strengths and identifying areas that need further review. It also offers detailed explanations for any incorrect answers.

item.title: Former CEO of celeb fav gym Dogpound launches $5M fund to back wellness companies
item.dc:creator: Dominic-Madori Davis
item.description: Jenny Liu is a solo first-time GP looking to back underrepresented wellness founders.

item.title: Struggling fusion power company General Fusion to go public via $1B reverse merger
item.dc:creator: Tim De Chant
item.description: General Fusion's merger with an acquisition company will net the company over $300 million. Just last year, the company ran into trouble raising money from other investors.

item.title: Waymo continues robotaxi ramp up with Miami service now open to public
item.dc:creator: Kirsten Korosec
item.description: Waymo is opening its driverless robotaxis to the public in Miami, starting with a 60-square-mile service area and plans to reach the airport "soon."
